 =======

 aka
 Orfeu negro

 Marcel Camus' Black Orpheus brings the ancient Greek myth of
 Orpheus and Eurydice to the twentieth-century madness of Carnival in Rio de
 Janeiro.
 With its eye-popping photography and ravishing, epochal soundtrack, Black
 Orpheus was an international cultural event, and it kicked off the bossa
 nova craze that set hi-fis across America spinning.
